## 11. Component API (Developer Reference)

### Checkbox Props

| Property        | Type                                          | Default      | Description                                           |
|-----------------|-----------------------------------------------|--------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| `checked`       | `boolean`                                     | `false`      | Determines if the checkbox is selected (controlled)   |
| `defaultChecked`| `boolean`                                     | `false`      | Initial checked state (uncontrolled)                  |
| `indeterminate` | `boolean`                                     | `false`      | Displays the partial/indeterminate indicator           |
| `disabled`      | `boolean`                                     | `false`      | Prevents interaction                                  |
| `required`      | `boolean`                                     | `false`      | Marks the checkbox as required for form validation    |
| `variant`       | `'standard' \| 'blue' \| 'green' \| 'dlv-red'` | `'standard'` | Color variant when checked                            |
| `size`          | `'sm' \| 'md' \| 'lg'`                        | `'md'`       | Checkbox size                                         |
| `style`         | `'box' \| 'rounded'`                          | `'box'`      | Shape style of the checkbox container                 |
| `label`         | `string`                                      | —            | Label text displayed next to the checkbox             |
| `helperText`    | `string`                                      | —            | Supporting description below the label                |
| `error`         | `string`                                      | —            | Error message displayed in error state                |
| `name`          | `string`                                      | —            | Form field name                                       |
| `value`         | `string`                                      | —            | Form field value                                      |
| `onChange`      | `(event: ChangeEvent) => void`                | —            | Callback fired when the checkbox state changes        |
| `className`     | `string`                                      | —            | Additional CSS class names                            |
| `aria-label`    | `string`                                      | —            | Accessible label (when no visible label is provided)  |
| `aria-describedby` | `string`                                  | —            | ID of element describing the checkbox                 |

### CheckboxGroup Props

| Property        | Type                                          | Default      | Description                                           |
|-----------------|-----------------------------------------------|--------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| `label`         | `string`                                      | —            | Group heading text (rendered as `<legend>`)           |
| `helperText`    | `string`                                      | —            | Supporting text for the group                         |
| `error`         | `string`                                      | —            | Group-level error message                             |
| `disabled`      | `boolean`                                     | `false`      | Disables all checkboxes in the group                  |
| `required`      | `boolean`                                     | `false`      | At least one checkbox must be selected                |
| `children`      | `ReactNode`                                   | —            | Checkbox components within the group                  |

---

## 12. Implementation Guidelines

### 12.1 Semantic HTML

Always use native `<input type="checkbox">` for proper semantics, keyboard support, and screen reader compatibility. Custom implementations must replicate all native behaviors and ARIA attributes.

```html
<label>
  <input type="checkbox" name="terms" required />
  I accept the terms and conditions
</label>
```

### 12.2 Controlled vs Uncontrolled

**Controlled**: State managed by parent component via `checked` and `onChange` props.

```jsx
const [checked, setChecked] = useState(false);
<Checkbox checked={checked} onChange={(e) => setChecked(e.target.checked)} />
```

**Uncontrolled**: State managed internally via `defaultChecked`. Access value via ref or form submission.

```jsx
<Checkbox defaultChecked={true} name="newsletter" />
```

### 12.3 Indeterminate State

The indeterminate state cannot be set via HTML attributes. It must be set programmatically via a ref:

```jsx
const ref = useRef(null);
useEffect(() => {
  if (ref.current) {
    ref.current.indeterminate = isIndeterminate;
  }
}, [isIndeterminate]);
```

### 12.4 Form Validation

- Use the `required` prop to enforce selection
- Validate on form submission by default
- Display error messages via the `error` prop
- Clear error state when the user checks the required checkbox
- For group validation, enforce minimum/maximum selections at the group level

### 12.5 Edge Cases

- **Rapid toggling**: Debounce `onChange` if it triggers expensive operations
- **Dynamic options**: When checkbox options are loaded asynchronously, preserve existing selections
- **Form reset**: Ensure checkboxes return to their `defaultChecked` state on form reset
- **SSR**: Indeterminate state must be set client-side (not available in server-rendered HTML)
- **Long labels**: Labels should wrap gracefully; checkbox aligns to the top of the first line

---

## 13. Usage Examples

### 13.1 Form Input Selection

```jsx
<form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
  <Checkbox label="I accept the terms and conditions" required />
  <Button type="submit" variant="primary">Continue</Button>
</form>
```

### 13.2 Preference Settings

```jsx
<CheckboxGroup label="Email preferences">
  <Checkbox label="Product updates" defaultChecked />
  <Checkbox label="Marketing emails" />
  <Checkbox label="Security alerts" defaultChecked disabled />
</CheckboxGroup>
```

### 13.3 Multi-Select Filters

```jsx
<CheckboxGroup label="Category">
  <Checkbox label="Electronics" value="electronics" />
  <Checkbox label="Clothing" value="clothing" />
  <Checkbox label="Books" value="books" />
  <Checkbox label="Home & Garden" value="home" />
</CheckboxGroup>
```

### 13.4 Permission Selection

```jsx
<CheckboxGroup label="User permissions" helperText="Select the access levels for this role">
  <Checkbox label="View dashboard" value="view" />
  <Checkbox label="Edit content" value="edit" />
  <Checkbox label="Manage users" value="manage" />
  <Checkbox label="Admin access" value="admin" />
</CheckboxGroup>
```

### 13.5 Bulk Selection in Tables

```jsx
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>
        <Checkbox
          aria-label="Select all rows"
          checked={allSelected}
          indeterminate={someSelected && !allSelected}
          onChange={handleSelectAll}
        />
      </th>
      <th>Name</th>
      <th>Status</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {rows.map((row) => (
      <tr key={row.id}>
        <td>
          <Checkbox
            aria-label={`Select ${row.name}`}
            checked={selectedIds.includes(row.id)}
            onChange={() => handleToggleRow(row.id)}
          />
        </td>
        <td>{row.name}</td>
        <td>{row.status}</td>
      </tr>
    ))}
  </tbody>
</table>
```

---

## 14. Do's and Don'ts

### Do

- ✓ Use clear, descriptive labels that explain the option
- ✓ Group related checkboxes together under a shared heading
- ✓ Maintain consistent spacing between checkboxes (8px vertical)
- ✓ Use the indeterminate state for parent-child hierarchies
- ✓ Provide visible feedback when a checkbox is selected
- ✓ Associate every checkbox with a label (visible or `aria-label`)
- ✓ Use `<fieldset>` and `<legend>` for checkbox groups
- ✓ Ensure touch targets are at least 44 × 44px

### Don't

- ✗ Use checkboxes for single-choice selections (use radio buttons)
- ✗ Use vague or ambiguous labels (e.g., "Click here", "Option 1")
- ✗ Overcrowd checkbox lists without grouping or hierarchy
- ✗ Use checkboxes without labels (unless `aria-label` is provided)
- ✗ Mix color variants within the same form or group
- ✗ Hide important options inside long scrollable checkbox lists
- ✗ Use checkboxes for actions that take immediate effect (use toggle switch)
- ✗ Disable checkboxes without explaining why they are unavailable

---

## 15. Related Components

| Component              | Relationship                                                      |
|------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Radio Button**       | Use when only one option can be selected from a group             |
| **Toggle Switch**      | Use for binary settings that take immediate effect                |
| **Form Field**         | Wrapper component for form inputs including checkboxes            |
| **Select**             | Use for single selection from a long list of options              |
| **Multi-select Dropdown** | Use for multi-selection from a long list of options            |
| **Button**             | Use for triggering actions, not for selection                     |

